"35:7:9" : {s: 35, a: 7, w: 9, r: "صلح", t: "ٱلصَّٰلِحَٰتِ", l: "صَّٰلِحَٰت", lc: 62, tl: "l-ṣāliḥāti", lb: "সৎ কাজ",e: "righteous deeds", b: "নেকীর", i: "kebajikan/saleh", f: 59, rm: "to be right/good/honest/upright/sound/righteous, suit, fit. aslaha - to set a thing aright, reform, do good. saalihaat - good works, fit and suiting deeds. aslaha (vb. 4) - to make whole sound, set things right, effect an agreement between, render fit. islaah - uprightness, reconciliation, amendment, reformation. muslihun - reformer, one who is upright, righteous, a person of integrity, peacemaker, suitable."},
